{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb8c90614-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s435"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"435"},"text":"§ 435.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Contracts in excess of specific appropriation","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Whoever, being an officer or employee of the United States, knowingly contracts for the erection, repair, or furnishing of any public building, or for any public improvement, to pay a larger amount than the specific sum appropriated for such purpose, shall be fined under this title ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002035"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002035"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" See 1994 Amendment note below."}],"tail":" or imprisoned not more than one year, or both."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb8c90615-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1948-06-25/ch645"},"text":"June 25, 1948, ch. 645","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/62/703"},"text":"62 Stat. 703","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/322/tXXXIII/s330016/1/K"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–322, title XXXIII, § 330016(1)(K)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-09-13"},"text":"Sept. 13, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/2147"},"text":"108 Stat. 2147","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb8c90616-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idb8c90617-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Based on title 18, U.S.C., 1940 ed., § 184 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1909-03-04/ch321/s98"},"text":"Mar. 4, 1909, ch. 321, § 98","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/35/1106"},"text":"35 Stat. 1106","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Words “or employee” were inserted to remove any ambiguity as to scope of section.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The offense described in this section involves no moral turpitude, and therefore the punishment provisions were reduced from $2,000 to $1,000 and from 2 years to 1 year, so that the stigma of a felony would not attach to an offender. (See classification of felony and misdemeanor in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t18/s1"},"text":"section 1 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and note thereunder.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Mandatory punishment provisions were rephrased in the alternative.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Changes were also made in phraseology.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb8c90618-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idb8c90619-47c4-11f1-9a61-b1559996dfe8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1994—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/322"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–322","children":[],"tail":", which directed the amendment of this section by substituting “fined under this title” for “fined not more than $5,000”, was executed by making the substitution for “fined not more than $1,000”, to reflect the probable intent of Congress."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
